      "content": "A systematic review in PubMed (DOI: 10.3389/fimmu.2021.631291) identified multiple trials showing that small-molecule inhibitors and biological agents targeting the IL-17 pathway can downregulate NF-κB signaling in rheumatoid arthritis, supporting the concept that modulating IL-17 leads to therapeutic effects partially mediated by NF-κB inhibition.",
      "justification": "We consulted PubMed to obtain peer-reviewed evidence on how novel treatments targeting IL-17 affect NF-κB in rheumatoid arthritis.",
